					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13596652#post-4734026</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13596652/scp-5185#post-4734026</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 30 Jul 2020 12:15:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Banazir</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6677746</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I definitely like this SCP. I always like it when we get a glimpse into dado's personal life - even if it's just a minor thing like being afraid of spiders. There's a few really, <em>really</em> minor things that kinda bother me though, especially this one sentence:</p> <blockquote> <p>Each instance has since grown to the size of a border collie (45.72&#160;cm - 55.88&#160;cm tall)</p> </blockquote> <p>The Foundation knows the exact size, even down to the second decimal place? How did they figure out so precisely? If I was a researcher assigned to 5185, and I had to put down their size in an official document, I would just say &quot;approximately 46 - 56&#160;cm&quot;. More precise information would probably require someone to get close to 5185 to take exact measurements, and that would be kind of risky, since you've said that 5185 are aggressive towards staff.<br /> Moreover: Are border collies the only dogs that size? Because saying &quot;the spiders are the size of a border collie&quot; sounds a little strange to me - why would that be the first connection the Foundation makes?<br /> Also - Can a spider really look at something &quot;inquisitively&quot;?</p> <p>Again, as I said before, those are really, really minor nitpicks, which definitely won't stop me from upvoting the article. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
